description:
Salary $94,000 - $104,000 + BONUS
.
At **MMGY Global,** we believe nothing shapes your view of the world like travel. So every day, we share our client’s stories from a perspective that inspires people to see the world differently. Our personalized service and strategy connect media, consumers and influencers across the globe, taking people to new places and changing their view for the better. At MMGY we inspire people to go places.
.
With established offices in Los Angeles and New York City our division develops strategic plans for our clients across consumer marketing, public relations, social media and travel trade engagement. The Account Director is responsible for leading the strategy and day-to-day activities and relationships of a portfolio of travel and tourism clients. We are seeking a strong leader who thrives under pressure, and who is an expert at cultivating strong business partnerships with clients and travel industry partners. This individual must be strategic, highly-organized, and driven to achieve.
.
Responsibilities include, but are not limited to:* Daily management of account teams across tourist board and product clients
* Develop and facilitate multi-year strategic marketing plans that lead to destination visitation growth for our tourist board clients;
* Apply knowledge of travel trade engagement, public relations, partnership & consumer marketing, social media and event management to all client activities;
* Lead team and client meetings;
* Establish and manage client budget and achieve agency billing goals;
* Integrate the efforts of all team members to optimize client plan results;
* Cultivate team mentality and build strong mutual trust between client and agency;
* Develop industry partnerships for the benefit of the client and agency:
* Overseeing client KPI goals to ensure targets are meet:
* Participate in business development initiatives:
* Manage staff resources, time allocations, annual reviews:
* Domestic and international travel is required.



Experience Requirements:* 10+ years of agency or tourist board experience at a senior level
* Experience in hospitality/travel industry required;
* Experience managing direct reports;
* Experience in working for or managing international tourist boards strongly desired;
* Strategic marketing experience strongly desired;
* Excellent understanding of marketing metrics;
* Excellent understand of travel trade distribution and partnerships;
* Must be highly effective at mentoring junior staff members;
* Strong leadership skills and ability to establish trust and partnerships;
* Excellent phone, verbal and written communication skills;
* Senior-level presentation skills are a must;
* Proofreading and attention to detail;
* Comfortable working under tight deadlines
* Comfortable working across different time zones as required
* Able to travel domestically and internationally for approximately 15% of the year
* Familiarity with Microsoft Office and IOS software



Education Requirements:* 4-year college degree

*This job description indicates the general nature and level of work expected of the* *Account Director.* *It is not designed to cover or contain a comprehensive listing of activities, duties or responsibilities.*
.**MMGY Global provides a comprehensive PTO + benefits package inclusive of a hybrid telework policy. Applicants for employment in the U.S. must possess work authorization which does not require sponsorship by the employer for a visa. MMGY Global is an Equal Opportunity Employer.**
.**Who Are We? We’re a travel-obsessed collective of more than 600 people across the country and around the globe. And when we say we inspire people to go places, we mean ALL people. That’s why we’re focused on nurturing a workforce that’s as diverse as the places we visit — welcoming candidates of all ages, genders and gender identities; ethnicities and religions; people of color; LGBTQIA+ people and their allies; working parents; veterans; and those with disabilities.**
